The paper deals with Visual Commonsense Reasoning, which involves understanding images and reasoning about them. This falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. The paper proposes an end-to-end trainable model that considers both answers and their reasons jointly, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also involves predicting rationales, which falls under the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) category. The paper also discusses different approaches for training the model, which involves optimization and learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed model in robotics (cs.RO).
